ngram
------------------------------------------
The OpenGrm NGram library is used for making and modifying n-gram language
models encoded as weighted finite-state transducers (FSTs). It makes use of
functionality in the OpenFst library to create, access and manipulate n-gram
models. Operations for counting, smoothing, pruning, applying, and evaluating
models as well as support for distributed computation are among those provided.
It was developed by contributors from OHSU and Google Research. It is an open
source project distributed under the Apache license.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.203.gf78009cb1ccf
  libfst26-1.8.3-1bl1
  libngram1316-1.3.16-1bl1
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libfst-devel-1.8.3-1bl1
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.openfst.org/twiki/bin/view/GRM/NGramLibrary

Canonical download:
  https://www.openfst.org/twiki/pub/GRM/NGramDownload/ngram-1.3.16.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ngram-1.3.16-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ngram-1.3.16-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ngram-1.3.16-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ngram-1.3.16-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libngram1316-1.3.16-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libngram-devel-1.3.16-X.tar.xz

